353
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:16,540
听着  弗兰克  我只想要你
Listen, Frank, all I'm asking is that

354
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:17,310
跟他们唱反调
you play devil's advocate with them.

355
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:19,690
对不起  给我点时间  我有点要紧事
Sorry, excuse me for a moment. This is important.

356
00:17:19,690 --> 00:17:20,820
这事我很在乎的  弗兰克
I don't want to short-shrift this, Frank.

357
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:21,830
我知道  先让我发完这条短信
No, I know, but I just have to send this text.

358
00:17:21,830 --> 00:17:23,450
我也不是闲人
I am busy too.

359
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:38,900
-请给我订靠过道的座位  -好的
- Make sure that's an aisle seat. - Of course.

360
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:41,550
我觉着你根本不重视这事
I don't feel as if you're taking this very seriously.

361
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:43,630
琳达  我向你道歉  对不起
Linda, I apologize. I am sorry.

362
00:17:43,630 --> 00:17:46,860
你说得没错  我没有敷衍你的意思
You are absolutely right, I did not mean to sound curt.

363
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:49,480
你是对的  这是很重要
And you are right, this is important.

364
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,270
咱俩这就好好谈谈你的提案
You and I should go through your proposal

365
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:53,650
仔细推敲每一个细节
and discuss it right down to the last detail.

366
00:17:53,650 --> 00:17:56,290
我没想让你逐字逐句地看
I am not asking you to go through it page by page,

367
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:58,840
只要帮忙让他们愿意认真考虑就行
just to help me initiate some meaningful dialogue.

368
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:02,530
-我当然会帮你了  琳达  -多谢你
- You can count on my help, Linda. - Thank you.

369
00:18:02,530 --> 00:18:06,300
-我会让排程员联系你这边  -好的  琳达
- I will have my scheduler reach out to yours. - Thank you, Linda.

370
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:09,070
请接内线
Get me a secure line, please.

371
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:14,210
副总统来电
The vice president is on the line.

372
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,510
副总统先生
Mr. Vice President.

373
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:24,650
通常我会无视你的来电  但我今天心情不错
Normally, I would ignore your call, but I am in a good mood today.

374
00:18:24,650 --> 00:18:25,780
你都没法破坏
Not even you could ruin it.

375
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:28,400
你是不是在向共和党捐款
Are you funneling money to the Republicans?

376
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:30,380
你到底在说什么
What on earth are you talking about?

377
00:18:30,380 --> 00:18:32,780
给了共和党超级政治行动委员会大概两千万
About 20 million in GOP Super PACs.

378
00:18:32,780 --> 00:18:35,550
你知道我从不给政党捐款
Now you know I never make political contributions.

379
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:37,680
很容易让我的投资者不高兴
That's the fastest way to upset my investors.

380
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:40,090
我知道钱的来路 是密苏里的一家赌场
I know the money is coming from a casino in Missouri

381
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:41,290
我还知道是冯给的
and I know it's from Feng.

382
00:18:41,290 --> 00:18:44,300
冯先生和我只合作过一次
Mr. Feng and I have one co-venture together,

383
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:45,710
而且和赌博毫无关系
and it has nothing to do with gambling.

384
00:18:45,710 --> 00:18:49,800
他的一架私人飞机定期飞往拉尼根的赌场
A plane that he owns flies to Lanagin's casino on a regular basis.

385
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:52,430
他私人时间做什么  与我无关
What he does on his own time is no business of mine.

386
00:18:52,430 --> 00:18:54,920
你是想给领导层添乱吗
Are you trying to create chaos in the ranks?

387
00:18:55,970 --> 00:19:00,010
共和党没有我的帮助似乎也做到了
The Republicans appear to be doing a fine job of that without my help.

388
00:19:00,010 --> 00:19:01,200
你不会得逞的  雷蒙德
Well, it's not gonna work, Raymond.

389
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:04,050
这只会让民主党更团结  而不是分裂
It'll bind the democrats together, not pull us apart.

390
00:19:04,050 --> 00:19:06,970
要我猜的话  过去十年里让民主党团结的
What has bound them together the past decade has been

391
00:19:06,970 --> 00:19:10,780
是资助你们成为多数党的捐助
the means to achieve a majority, if I had to guess...

392
00:19:10,780 --> 00:19:12,450
是他用钱铸就了国会
He stacked Congress.

393
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:14,680
铸就了我任党鞭的多数党
The majority I whipped.

394
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:20,370
原来一直是你在操纵  雷蒙德
So it's been you, Raymond, all along,

395
00:19:20,370 --> 00:19:22,850
拉尼根的钱流向我们的时候也是
even when Lanagin's money was coming to us.

396
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:27,570
你总在做我已经否认的假设
You keep making assumptions that I have denied.

397
00:19:27,570 --> 00:19:28,930
等季度报告一出来
Once the quarterly filings come out,

398
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:31,280
有电脑的人都会明白是怎么回事
anybody with a laptop is gonna see what's going on.

399
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:33,630
那是在九月底
The end of September.

400
00:19:33,690 --> 00:19:38,280
还早着呢  但我很期待看到那些报告
That's a long way off. But I look forward to seeing the reports.

401
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:40,980
在中期选举两周前
Should make for some very interesting reading

402
00:19:41,540 --> 00:19:43,520
那肯定是很有趣的读物
two weeks before the midterms.

403
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:46,410
你别想靠恐吓回到决策桌上  雷蒙德
You cannot bully your way back to the table, Raymond,

404
00:19:46,410 --> 00:19:48,850
你也休想收买国会
just as you cannot buy the keys to Congress.

405
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:52,230
祝你成功维持众议院多数席位
Best of luck keeping your majority in the House.

406
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:55,130
我知道那对你来说意义重大
I know how much it means to you.

407
00:19:57,590 --> 00:20:00,830
有钱给你用的时候  大家都不会多想
When the money's coming your way, you don't ask any questions.

408
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:05,240
但这下清楚了  拉尼根不过是个幌子
But now it's clear. Lanagin's never been anything but a front.

409
00:20:05,590 --> 00:20:09,000
我要告诉总统吗  不
Do I tell the president? No.

410
00:20:09,170 --> 00:20:10,470
他会想我之前怎么不知道
He'll wonder why I didn't know,

411
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:11,670
那我就显得消息不灵了
which makes me look uninformed,

412
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,860
或者他会责备传话的人  把他也卷进去
or he'll blame the messenger for involving him,

413
00:20:13,860 --> 00:20:15,570
那就显得我太大意了
which makes me look careless.

414
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:19,730
我知道这是个陷阱  我得守住这个秘密
I know it's a trap. I must keep this to myself.

415
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:22,830
他问你代表谁进行购买
He wants to know who you are buying on behalf of.

416
00:20:22,830 --> 00:20:25,720
一家名叫水星资本的对冲基金  还没上市
It's a hedge fund named Mercury Capital. It's unlisted.

417
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:36,120
他们需要主要投资者的名字
They need the names of the principal investors.

418
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:37,970
告诉他我得保护他们的身份
Tell him I have to protect identities.

419
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:45,060
代理人需要更多信息  他要完整的投资人名单
The broker needs more. He wants a full investor list.

420
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:46,500
跟他说
Say, um...

421
00:20:47,620 --> 00:20:50,560
就说主要投资者和白宫联系密切
Say that the principal investor has strong ties to the White House.

422
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:59,390
他们问你是不是代表克雷顿-维斯特
And they want to know if you represent Clayton West.

423
00:20:59,390 --> 00:21:00,640
克雷顿-维斯特吗
Clayton West?

424
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:09,400
-他还在等  -稍候
- He's waiting. - One second.

425
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,270
上面写了些什么
What does it say?

426
00:21:14,370 --> 00:21:21,760
是关于一家中国的稀土精炼厂
It's about a refinery in China for rare earth elements.

427
00:21:22,470 --> 00:21:26,670
跟他说是  告诉他主要投资者是雷蒙德·塔斯克
Tell him yes. Tell him the principal investor is Raymond Tusk.

428
00:21:39,270 --> 00:21:40,610
我是道格·斯坦普
This is Doug Stamper...

429
00:21:43,410 --> 00:21:46,710
-我们该用什么招待沃克夫妇  -氰化物
- What should we serve the Walkers? - Cyanide.

430
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,830
用来做甜点好了  主餐呢
Saving that for dessert. What about a main course?

431
00:21:50,830 --> 00:21:54,960
哪种肉  或是蔬菜
Meat of some sort? Vegetables?

432
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,510
我实在不太擅长这方面
I mean, this isn't really my area of expertise.

433
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,890
我在想  不如找弗莱迪来
I was thinking, what about Freddy?

434
00:22:02,860 --> 00:22:05,620
-吃肋排吗  -这样会不会太唐突
- Ribs? - Or is that gauche?

435
00:22:06,810 --> 00:22:10,930
不会  我喜欢这主意
No. I like the idea.

436
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:16,510
我们可以用高档瓷器  精致配菜
Well, we can do the nice china, gourmet sides,

437
00:22:16,510 --> 00:22:19,010
但我觉得肋排更有人情味
but I think the ribs make it more personal.

438
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:20,990
我去打电话
I'll make the call.

439
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:25,750
-你正在等的这通电话有消息吗  -还没有
- Any word on the call you're expecting? - Not yet.

440
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,750
我想他的航班应该还没到
I don't think he's landed.

441
00:22:29,230 --> 00:22:31,610
你还真搭起来了啊
This is really coming along, isn't it?

442
00:22:32,420 --> 00:22:34,240
你觉得小孩子气
You think it's childish.

443
00:22:34,890 --> 00:22:37,010
总比打游戏好
I think it's better than video games.

444
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:55,930
把我的五千美金支票带来了吗
Do you have my check for $5,000?

445
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:58,240
等我涨工资了再说吧
Next time when I get a raise.

446
00:22:59,630 --> 00:23:01,110
在赌场运气不好吗
Bad luck at the casino?

447
00:23:02,410 --> 00:23:03,880
塔斯克知道我在这儿
So Tusk knows I'm here.

448
00:23:03,940 --> 00:23:07,380
-丹尼尔·拉尼根知道  -塔斯克跟这事有关吗
- Daniel Lanagin knows you're here. - Is Tusk involved?

449
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:09,070
我为什么要承认
Why would I admit that?

450
00:23:09,510 --> 00:23:11,040
塔斯克和你有生意来往
Tusk is in business with you.

451
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:12,420
你在给拉尼根汇钱
You're sending money to Lanagin.

452
00:23:12,420 --> 00:23:14,990
拉尼根的赌场离塔斯克很近
Lanagin's casino is in Tusk's backyard.

453
00:23:14,990 --> 00:23:16,080
你大老远飞来
You didn't fly halfway around the

454
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:18,160
不会就是为了证实猜测吧
world just to confirm suspicions.

455
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:20,230
告诉我你想要什么
Tell me what you want.

456
00:23:20,230 --> 00:23:22,490
我们想中止资金继续流向共和党
We want the money to stop flowing to the Republicans.

457
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:23,810
我有什么好处
And what do I receive?

458
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:26,340
我说了我们想要的  现在到你了
I've told you what we want. Now it's your turn.

459
00:23:26,340 --> 00:23:28,650
好让你再次误导我吗
Ah, so you can mislead me again.

460
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:33,340
形势变了  误导你对我们没有好处
Things have changed. We have nothing to gain by misleading you.

461
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,490
你觉得我的花园如何
What do you think of my garden?

462
00:23:39,970 --> 00:23:41,220
非常漂亮
It's very beautiful.

463
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:45,350
只知道谈生意  就会忘记欣赏美景
When you only talk business, you stop appreciating beauty.

464
00:23:45,910 --> 00:23:47,660
我没什么时间赏景
I don't have much time for beauty.

465
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:49,620
真可惜
That's a shame.

466
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:51,900
为了让你们这些老板有闲暇赏景
For people like you to smell the flowers,

467
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:53,550
我们这些手下得去除杂草
some of us have to pull the weeds.

468
00:23:54,780 --> 00:23:58,360
-打算什么时候走  -还没买回程票
- When do you plan on leaving? - I haven't bought my return ticket yet.

469
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,160
很好
Good.

470
00:24:00,780 --> 00:24:02,220
我需要考虑一晚
I'd like to think on this for a night.

471
00:24:02,550 --> 00:24:04,200
我想你一定累坏了
And I'm sure you must be exhausted.

472
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:06,100
可否赏脸在这儿做客
Would you do me the honor of being my guest?

473
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:10,600
-非常感谢  -很好  你能休息一下了
- I'd be very grateful. - Excellent. You can get some rest.

474
00:24:11,090 --> 00:24:11,970
你要是喜欢
And if you like,

475
00:24:12,650 --> 00:24:14,940
这里还有很多美的事物可以享受
there are many beautiful things to enjoy here.

476
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:20,320
请
Please.

477
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:54,490
先生  格雷森先生到了 
Sir, Mr. Grayson is here.

478
00:24:54,950 --> 00:24:55,930
赛斯
Seth.

479
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:59,300
你上任以来我们还一直没机会
You and I haven't really properly had the chance to sit

480
00:24:59,300 --> 00:25:01,460
好好坐下聊聊
and have a chat since you came on board.

481
00:25:01,460 --> 00:25:03,390
有什么需要我改进的吗  先生
Is there anything I can be doing better, sir?

482
00:25:03,390 --> 00:25:05,900
没有  你很厉害
No. No. I'm impressed.

483
00:25:05,930 --> 00:25:08,440
你很聪明  也有很好的职业素养
You're very smart. Excellent work ethic.

484
00:25:09,620 --> 00:25:13,170
但更重要的是  你的洞察力很强
But more importantly, you're very observant.

485
00:25:13,230 --> 00:25:14,690
信息就是力量
Information is power.

486
00:25:15,530 --> 00:25:20,210
就是在这间屋子里  我妻子向世人
It was right here in this room that my wife revealed a great deal

487
00:25:20,210 --> 00:25:23,590
吐露了惊人的消息  成千上万的人
of information to a great number of people. Millions of them.

488
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:26,300
先生  如果你是担心我所知道的事
Sir, if your concern is my knowledge of any discrepancies,

489
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:27,050
我向你保证
then let me assure you --

490
00:25:27,060 --> 00:25:29,100
克莱尔和我都很注重隐私
Claire and I are very private people.

491
00:25:29,890 --> 00:25:32,170
我明白你为何会不信任我
I can understand why you might mistrust me.

492
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:35,310
我也有敏锐的洞察力  就像你  赛斯
I'm also observant, like you, Seth.

493
00:25:36,370 --> 00:25:38,540
但我还是会有盲点
But I still have my blind spots.

494
00:25:39,540 --> 00:25:43,290
我绝不会想到去找马博利太太
It would have never occurred to me to reach out to Mrs. Marbury.

495
00:25:44,770 --> 00:25:48,400
她丈夫去世了  也没留记录
Her husband was dead. He kept no records.

496
00:25:49,510 --> 00:25:53,460
但你还是找到了  白纸黑字
And yet there it was, in black and white.

497
00:25:55,390 --> 00:25:57,510
我很感谢你把它交给我们
I respect the fact that you brought it to us.

498
00:25:57,510 --> 00:26:00,300
这也是我们为什么会录用你
That's what got you in the door.

499
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:04,770
但想要留下  这还不够
But if you want to stay, I need more.

500
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:12,460
你到底是什么居心
What exactly are you up to?

501
00:26:14,690 --> 00:26:16,420
我受雇于雷米·丹顿
I was hired by Remy Danton.

502
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:19,330
他要我来找你们的把柄
He wants anything damaging that I can find.

503
00:26:22,330 --> 00:26:24,400
-他有日记的备份吗  -没有
- Does he have a copy of the journal? - No copies.

504
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:25,940
我把原件交给了安德伍德夫人
I gave the original to Mrs. Underwood,

505
00:26:25,950 --> 00:26:28,140
我告诉他  她的话属实
and I told him that her story checks out.

506
00:26:28,340 --> 00:26:30,880
-你还给了他什么  -我手上没别的了
- Did you give him anything else? - I don't have anything else.

507
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,290
就算有我也不会给他
I wouldn't give it to him if I did.

508
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:34,270
为什么你现在才说
Why am I only hearing about this now?

509
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:36,230
你是美利坚合众国的副总统
Well, you're the vice president of the United States.

510
00:26:36,230 --> 00:26:38,300
雷米在为雷蒙德·塔斯克卖命
Remy works for Raymond Tusk.

511
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:40,860
我夹在了两位极有权势的人之间
That puts me between two extremely powerful people.

512
00:26:41,410 --> 00:26:42,540
得小心为好
I had to be careful.

513
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:45,840
雷米肯定答应给你一大笔钱吧
I'm sure that Remy's offering you a great deal of money.

514
00:26:45,910 --> 00:26:47,260
但他只能给钱
But that's all he offers.

515
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:50,930
我看到你在参议院推动福利改革法案时
When I saw you push entitlement reform through the Senate,

516
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:54,500
立刻就明白了谁才是白宫最有权力的人
it was clear to me where the real power in the White House is.

517
00:26:55,090 --> 00:26:58,490
我想为你这样的人效力  不是乘游艇兜风
I want to work for a man like you, not sail a yacht.

518
